<i>in just a few moments now,</i>

72
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:54,325
<i>President Nixon</i>
<i>will be appearing</i>
<i>before the people,</i>

73
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:58,302
<i>perhaps for the last</i>
<i>time as President</i>
<i>of the United States.</i>

74
00:03:59,672 --> 00:04:01,867
<i>15 seconds, Mr. President.</i>

75
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:11,444
Okay, that's five,
four, three...

76
00:04:15,288 --> 00:04:18,416
Good evening.
This is the 37th time

77
00:04:18,491 --> 00:04:21,221
I have spoken to you
from this office

78
00:04:21,294 --> 00:04:23,854
where so many decisions
have been made

79
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:26,455
that have shaped
the history of our nation.

80
00:04:26,532 --> 00:04:28,523
I remember exactly
where I was.

81
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:33,303
My father called.
The phone rang, my father
called and he said,

82
00:04:33,373 --> 00:04:36,638
"Turn on the TV right now.
Richard Nixon's going down."

83
00:04:36,709 --> 00:04:40,440
I was at home with friends,
and we were watching
television at home.

84
00:04:40,513 --> 00:04:43,311
We stayed up and,
like everyone else,
I'd been glued to

85
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:45,874
the Select and Judiciary
Committee hearings
night after night.

86
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,079
And then finally,
it had come to this.

87
00:04:48,154 --> 00:04:53,956
Therefore, I shall resign
the presidency effective
at noon tomorrow.

88
00:04:54,027 --> 00:04:57,019
But instead of
the satisfaction
I imagined I'd feel,

89
00:04:57,096 --> 00:04:59,360
I just got angrier
and angrier,

90
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:02,196
because there was
no admission of guilt.

91
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:03,701
There was no apology.

92
00:05:03,770 --> 00:05:05,169
Little did I know

93
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:07,365
that I would one day
be part of the team

94
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,840
that would try and
elicit that apology.

95
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:12,935
<i>To leave office
before my term is completed</i>

96
00:05:13,012 --> 00:05:16,004
is abhorrent to every
instinct in my body.

97
00:05:16,082 --> 00:05:18,573
I have never been a quitter.

98
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:20,312
And that that team
would be led

99
00:05:20,386 --> 00:05:24,083
by the most unlikely
of white knights,

100
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,091
a man with no
political convictions
whatsoever,

101
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:30,391
a man who, as far as I know,
had never even voted
once in his life.

102
00:05:31,197 --> 00:05:35,327
But he was a man who had
one big advantage
over the rest of us.

103
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:38,900
He understood television.

104
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:50,508
<i>And now, the host of</i>
Frost Over Australia,

105
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:53,211
<i>Mr. David Frost!</i>

106
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:57,081
Thank you, thank you.

107
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:00,483
Hello. Good evening.

108
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:03,688
And with the eyes of the world
focused on the White House,

109
