136
00:07:15,168 --> 00:07:18,001
All right,
you blokes, let's get
the set broken down.

137
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:22,131
<i>Are witnesses to the saddest day</i>
<i>in the life of Richard Nixon,</i>

138
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:26,144
<i>his last moments</i>
<i>as President</i>
<i>of the United States,</i>

139
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:29,841
<i>a moment unlike</i>
<i>any other in the history</i>
<i>of this country.</i>

140
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,698
<i>Richard Nixon, who goes now</i>

141
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:51,032
<i>from the power</i>
<i>of the presidency</i>

142
00:07:51,103 --> 00:07:53,333
<i>to a form of exile</i>
<i>in California.</i>

143
00:07:53,406 --> 00:07:56,204
Find out the numbers
for this, will you?
Worldwide.

144
00:08:09,689 --> 00:08:11,589
<i>I remember his face.</i>

145
00:08:13,092 --> 00:08:15,424
<i>Staring out the window.</i>

146
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:20,159
<i>Down below him,</i>
<i>a liberal America</i>
<i>cheered, gloated.</i>

147
00:08:21,868 --> 00:08:24,393
Hippies, draft dodgers,
dilettantes,

148
