And what?
Come on, David.

175
00:10:01,534 --> 00:10:03,001
Surely the only thing
that would interest anyone

176
00:10:03,069 --> 00:10:05,401
about Richard Nixon
would be a confession.

177
00:10:05,471 --> 00:10:07,234
A full,
no-holds-barred
confession.

178
00:10:07,306 --> 00:10:09,536
Well, we'll get that, too.

179
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:10,598
From Richard Nixon?

180
00:10:10,676 --> 00:10:12,007
Come on, John.

181
00:10:12,078 --> 00:10:14,376
Just think of the
numbers it would get.

182
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,775
Do you know how
many people watched

183
00:10:16,849 --> 00:10:18,476
his farewell speech
in the White House?

184
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:20,576
Four hundred million.

185
00:10:21,954 --> 00:10:23,945
But in the end,
David heard nothing.

186
00:10:24,023 --> 00:10:25,684
And soon after
arriving in California,

187
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:29,353
Nixon was rushed
to hospital with an acute
attack of phlebitis.

188
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:45,242
<i>I think it was</i>
<i>around this time</i>
<i>that Gerald Ford,</i>

189
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:46,335
who was the new President,

190
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:48,471
and who was desperate
to move the agenda
on from Watergate,

191
00:10:48,547 --> 00:10:51,641
gave Nixon a full,
free and absolute pardon.

192
00:10:51,717 --> 00:10:54,447
<i>Now therefore, I,</i>
<i>Gerald R. Ford,</i>

193
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:57,182
<i>President of</i>
<i>the United States,</i>

194
00:10:57,256 --> 00:11:01,192
<i>have granted,</i>
<i>and by these presents</i>
<i>do grant,</i>

195
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:03,785
<i>a full,</i>
<i>free and absolute pardon</i>

196
00:11:03,863 --> 00:11:09,062
<i>unto Richard Nixon</i>
<i>for all offenses</i>
<i>against the United States.</i>

197
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:11,535
It meant that the man
who had committed
the greatest felony

198
00:11:11,604 --> 00:11:14,266
in American political history
would never stand trial.

199
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:16,740
It was like he slipped
out the back door.

200
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:19,740
<i>A public opinion</i>
<i>poll indicates</i>

201
00:11:19,812 --> 00:11:23,179
<i>a two-to-one disapproval</i>
<i>of the pardoning</i>
<i>of Richard Nixon.</i>

202
00:11:23,249 --> 00:11:26,446
<i>One telegram</i>
<i>from Virginia said,</i>
<i>"Roosevelt had his New Deal,</i>

203
